oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Some effects of water quality on the performance of high yielding cows in an arid climate
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Challis, D. J.
Zeinstra, J. S.
Anderson, M. J.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The water from wells in Saudi Arabia is often high in mineral content. The cows in this study had been receiving water containing between 4000 and 5000 ppm total dissolved solids. Full article published in Veterinary Record (1987) 120. 12-15
